Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Dates and versions", "Subsection",
 InitializationCell->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"e4dab842-7aff-47ab-8eba-b822db0adadc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["In V0.2.0:",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "\n-Reaction ",
 StyleBox["Be7(d,p)",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " is now tabulated in this external file and not given analytically and is \
taken from [Rij19]\n-Decoupling of neutrinos with oscillations (precomputed \
with NEVO, see [Froustey et al. 2020]).\n-Constants reevaluated with Particle \
Data Group 2020 data. Main change is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["G", "Newt"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7f39ba5d-efb5-4564-b2ca-b7d29a2615fb"],
 ".\n-QED corrections (pair production) to some nuclear rates included (see \
[Pitrou&Pospelov 2020]).\n-An option to use only reduced nuclear network has \
been added.\n-QED at order ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SuperscriptBox["e", "3"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "89fdbcfb-616a-489b-8736-5b62c2aae767"],
 ") included in plasma thermodynamics (reduces Neff by 0.001, see [Bennett et \
al. 2019])\n-Cosmological parameters are set to the last column of table 2 of \
[Planck 2018 VI].\n\n",
 StyleBox["In V0.2.1:",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "\n-New ",
 "dpg",
 " rate (reaction ",
 StyleBox["d + p <-> He3 + g",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ") in new reaction file BBNRatesAC2022.dat. \[LineSeparator]  Rate taken \
from Moscoso et al. 2021 \n\n",
 StyleBox["In V0.2.2:",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "\n-small modification to make it compatible with Mathematica 13.\n-neutron \
lifetime update with PDG 2023.\n\n",
 StyleBox["In V0.2.3:",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "\n- Possibility to add distortions in an analytic form (with all the \
caveats due to the fact that neutrino self scatter and scatter of \
electrons/positrons and cannot tolerate spectral distortions for T>2MeV in \
principle).\n- \[OpenCurlyQuote]Nrelat\[CloseCurlyQuote] parameter added \
(number of relativistic decoupled species). So as to separate neutrinos from \
other thermalized but decoupled  relativistic degrees of freedom.\n- Switched \
the mass database from nubase2016 to nubase2020\n- Values of physical \
constants from PDG 2024\n\n",
 StyleBox["In V0.3.0",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "\n- PRIMAT now looks more like a package even though it is not yet a \
Package. \nWhen loading PRIMAT-Main.m from an external notebook, this now \
only loads definitions (and takes 0.3 seconds), but no computation is \
performed. The user can then modify the various options about physics or \
numerics, and then call for the function which either perform one run \
(RunNumericalIntegrals) or a MonteCarlo estimation of errors \
(RunPRIMATMonteCarlo), and then read the results. Examples are provided in \
the Example folder. It has been tested under a variety of combination of \
options, but please reports situations in which this still generates bugs. \n\
- It now takes less than a second for the small network of reactions (12 \
reactions) and 16 seconds for the full network (434 reactions), provided the \
weak rates are precomputed and stored in the CSV folder (which takes place \
the first time).\n- There is a PythonInterface folder which explains how to \
call PRIMAT from python and how to read its results and modify its options. \
See readme file in that folder.\n- The most crucial functions for performing \
numerical integration are compiled and stored on disk. Hence after the first \
run, the loss in compiling these functions is avoided by reading the compiled \
functions which are stored in the lib folder. \n- A ",
 StyleBox["$Parthenope",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " option allows to replace the rates ",
 StyleBox["d+d <-> He3+n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (ddn) and ",
 StyleBox["d+d <-> t+p",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (ddp) with the ones used in Parthenope3.0 (Gariazzo et al. 2021).\n- The \
names of the folders in PRIMAT have changed.\n- Tested on Mac OS and with \
Mathematica 14 only.\n- Rate for ",
 StyleBox["d+a <-> Li6 + g",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " replaced by [Trezzi2017]. New reaction file BBNRatesAC2024.dat. \n"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.809769467131113*^9, {3.861100971346328*^9, 3.861101018716343*^9}, {
   3.8965451942970877`*^9, 3.8965452084773817`*^9}, {3.903079974733313*^9, 
