  3.861260482427253*^9, 3.861260482907577*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[1781]:=",ExpressionUUID->"9a07fb33-889d-4da2-a43e-778e2afe93fe"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If $QEDPlasmaCorrections is set to True, the QED corrections to the \
pressure and the energy density are taken into account. This affects for \
instance the expansion rate via the Friedmann equation. \nExpressions can be \
found in [Lopez&Turner 1998], [Mangano et al. 2001] or in [Heckler 1994]. See \
also the companion paper where Eqs. 48-52 are used inside Eq. 55 to modify \
the entropy and Eq. 58 to modify the energy density.\nIf $CompleteQEDPressure \
is False, the subdominant term is ignored. Otherwise it is included. We \
checked it is so subdominant that it does not change the results.\nIf $QEDOe3 \
is True, then order ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["e", "3"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "84334a77-0cd3-4752-8878-bb30a03fcbab"],
 " corrections to the Plasma (to P and \[Rho]) are included, Following [",
 StyleBox["Bennett et. al. 2019].",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.809769617071743*^9},ExpressionUUID->"59f3461f-ea4e-4b58-8289-\
eb2b2ae6e054"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"$RecomputePlasmaCorrections", "=", "False"}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.861101424879527*^9, 3.861101425464632*^9}, {
  3.861101460931744*^9, 3.8611014615066347`*^9}, {3.861259616291389*^9, 
  3.8612596167137012`*^9}, {3.861261714483686*^9, 3.86126171508357*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[1784]:=",ExpressionUUID->"61fe627e-5390-476f-8532-4ee97b7172bf"],

Cell["\<\
Since the QED effects depend on temperature, they need to be computed only \
once for all and they are stored on a file. But we can force the \
recomputation of these corrections by setting $RecomputePlasmaCorrections to \
True;\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.715961498733636*^9, 3.7159615450682487`*^9}, 
   3.7160054044238987`*^9, {3.716005435709878*^9, 
   3.716005439502181*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4b4bfe17-d50e-4974-9cb9-\
67b1e2d6bce4"]
}, Open  ]],

