  3.966056385521208*^9, 3.966056385849144*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[1786]:=",ExpressionUUID->"8541dc67-bc41-4f80-ac05-5e6f05f11391"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If $IncompleteNeutrinoDecoupling is set to True, the entropy transfer from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["e", "\[PlusMinus]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "45f3ac59-d71b-478e-9e51-680675f600f1"],
 " annihilations to neutrinos is taken into account. Indeed if we consider \
the details of the decoupling of neutrinos, it is found that decoupling is \
incomplete by the time electrons and positrons annihilate into photons. This \
results in a slight overheating of neutrinos and cooling of the \
electrons/photons plasma.\nThe advised value for \
$IncompleteNeutrinoDecoupling is True."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f59e5b0b-adfb-4848-9c6c-fb787314edf8"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"$NEVO", "=", "True"}], ";"}], " ", 
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Recommended", " ", "True"}], " ", "*)"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"$TrueT\[Nu]e", "=", "True"}], ";"}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Recommended", " ", "True"}], " ", "*)"}], 
  " "}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"$FileSuffix", "=", "\"\<\>\""}], ";"}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{
   "Suffix", " ", "of", " ", "the", " ", "file", " ", "name", " ", "in", " ", 
    "which", " ", "NEVO", " ", "results", " ", "are", " ", 
    RowBox[{"stored", "."}]}], " ", "*)"}]}]}], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8612595957967587`*^9, 3.86125959672474*^9}, {
  3.861261718541793*^9, 3.861261719004272*^9}, {3.934958598002645*^9, 
  3.934958602900876*^9}, {3.93512426372217*^9, 3.935124275318284*^9}, {
  3.935124984424987*^9, 3.935124985018446*^9}, {3.9351252820965767`*^9, 
