  3.9355766103233137`*^9, 3.9355766129508877`*^9}, {3.93619021565384*^9, 
  3.9361902475964727`*^9}, {3.952017086942451*^9, 3.95201708817278*^9}, {
  3.966056390055976*^9, 3.9660563904441013`*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[1787]:=",ExpressionUUID->"aac143ed-baab-47c1-93a4-4ab82afab28d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The original PRIMAT approach consisted in using a fit for the heating \
function of the neutrinos due to incomplete decoupling. The fitting functions \
which is used is the one given in [PArthENoPE]. It is used in Eq. 63 of the \
companion paper. In this approach, all three flavors of neutrinos have \
equilibrium distributions at a common temperature derived in Eq. 64 of the \
companion paper. This original method is chosen if $NEVO = False.\n\nHowever, \
if $NEVO is set to True, we directly import the neutrino effective \
temperatures (and the heating function) from the results obtained with NEVO, \
a Python code designed to implement neutrino evolution through the MeV age \
(developed by Julien Froustey and Cyril Pitrou, and described in [Froustey et \
al. 2020]). This enables to take into account two additional effects: the \
different decoupling of electron and muon/tau neutrinos, resulting in \
different effective temperatures (implemented if $TrueT\[Nu]e is set to True) \
and non-thermal distortions of the neutrinos distribution functions \
(implemented if $SpectralDistortions is set to True, see below).\n\n",
 StyleBox["Important:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " it would be inconsistent to set $SpectralDistortions = True but \
$IncompleteNeutrinoDecoupling = False, except if the are analytic distortions \
included (see below). That is why when computing the weak rates, spectral \
distortions are included only if both these options are set to True, or if \
$AnalyticDistortions is set to True.\nThe code checks for most obvious \
inconsistent options and modifies them (printing a warning message)\n\nThe \
common neutrino average temperature can therefore be computed in two \
different (but, in principle, equivalent) ways: \n1/ through the heating \
function \n2/ directly from the effective temperatures. \nIf $Taverage\
\[ScriptCapitalN] is set to True, the first method is used but we prefer the \
second method, hence we set it to False."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.934958655590507*^9, 3.9349586562887373`*^9}, {
  3.9351057867204037`*^9, 3.9351057872618113`*^9}, {3.935574516306354*^9, 
  3.9355745527379427`*^9}, {3.937273174495028*^9, 3.937273174998392*^9}, {
  3.9372734205974073`*^9, 3.9372734236645327`*^9}, {3.9372734842521048`*^9, 
  3.937273508807068*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c0bd8283-f157-4463-bbc0-\
701179458828"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"$Taverage\[ScriptCapitalN]", "=", "False"}], ";"}], 
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{"Recommended", " ", "False"}], " ", "*)"}]}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8612603029544983`*^9, 3.861260303433213*^9}, {
  3.861261729743487*^9, 3.861261730337091*^9}},
 CellLabel->
  "In[1790]:=",ExpressionUUID->"aac143ed-baab-47c1-93a4-4ab82afab28d"],

Cell["Files in which NEVO results are stored", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9363670165009947`*^9, 
  3.9363670264255667`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d0f84939-f216-499f-adcb-\
