Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Scale factor - temperature relation", "Section",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.693925431114146*^9, 3.693925438870551*^9}, {
  3.700387896282916*^9, 3.7003878972628403`*^9}, {3.936668594975305*^9, 
  3.936668603463122*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4eda6d66-c4be-4177-ab5f-\
93f1b92d04f2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the function which gives the scale factor as a function of the \
temperature. \n\n1) If neutrino decoupling is total, then the total entropy \
is conserved and so it is only a function of temperature (entropy density) \
and scale factor (volume), since S= s ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["a", "3"], "."}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "019496cf-077c-47c8-9525-0f8eeb067d91"],
 "So this can be solved without a differential equation in time. \n2) If \
Incomplete Neutrino decoupling is taken into account, we use the result aC \
previously obtained, that is we track the evolution of entropy, (see function \
SolveaOFTwhenID above)."
}], "Text",
 InitializationCell->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"aa41e527-bf89-4563-8ecb-2aa838f59f84"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"a", "[", "T_", "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{"If", "[", 
    RowBox[{"$IncompleteNeutrinoDecoupling", ",", 
     RowBox[{"aC", "[", "T", "]"}], ",", 
     FractionBox["TCMB0", 
      RowBox[{"T", " ", 
       SuperscriptBox[
        RowBox[{"DST", "[", "T", "]"}], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "/", "3"}], ")"}]]}]]}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.693923171260274*^9, 3.693923189555379*^9}, {
