Cell["\<\
We define the temperature as a function of time. Since we have T(a) \
(conserved entropy) and a(t) (Friedman equation), we just combine both.
In case of incomplete decoupling of neutrinos, we could not use conservation \
of entropy to get T(a) but we used the fit for the heating rate which allowed \
us to obtain numerically T(a) and a(T).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"441c7923-6a62-4eb4-9635-61d5c548e9bc"],

