Cell["\<\
NUBASE 2020 Syntax :
The first three characters of each line are the A. 
Characters from 5 to 7 are Z (but the 8th character is a number for a \
possible excited state. Hence we use character 5 to 8 for 10*Z, and then \
divide by 10. If it is an integer it is not an excited state. Otherwise it is \
discarded. This is a dirty hack)
From 19 to 31 it is mass excess.
From 89 to 102 it is some information on spin and parity.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.717579969237245*^9, 3.717580016288292*^9}, {
  3.717581039288995*^9, 3.717581040951882*^9}, {3.722697499636197*^9, 
  3.722697502999465*^9}, {3.935548292986759*^9, 3.9355483002600327`*^9}, {
