Cell["Formal construction of r.h.s", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.715951517895728*^9, 3.715951522261695*^9}, {
  3.722701105311162*^9, 
  3.722701109552939*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"dab0d30c-6896-474a-ae19-\
50caea25f311"],

Cell["\<\
This is a function which takes the list of reactions, with the specification \
of initial and final particles and their multiplicity, and builds the rhs of \
the differential system.
It builds the rhs of Eq 138 in companion paper.\
\>", "Text",
 InitializationCell->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"bb3a4ae2-be32-403a-9be4-f48e1b2caf51"],

Cell["Abstract abundance functions", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.715950176787857*^9, 3.715950189358015*^9}, {
  3.715950817680915*^9, 
  3.7159508193759747`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b39963f6-a614-4f0b-967e-\
b8400c2d70b8"],

Cell["\<\
We build list of abundance function and abundance function derivatives which \
are used later to build the system of equations. These stay at an abstract \
level and they are used only to build the differential system of equations \
which is later solved by NDSolve.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.698565973572652*^9, 3.6985659887226543`*^9}, {
  3.699848812725277*^9, 3.699848812840036*^9}, {3.715950055094767*^9, 
